    "long_instructions": "### Recreate Paris\r\n\r\n**Define:** You've been hired to recreate the backing track for *Paris* by The Chainsmokers. You can use tracks from the original song or mix in new sounds from other sound packs.\r\n\r\n**Prepare:** Plan out what instruments you want to include in each section. Think about how the two parts should sound different or build off each other. Decide where you might want to use a nested loop to repeat a pattern within one section. Listen to the example below for what this could sound like!\r\n\r\n**Try:** Add your first set of backing tracks under the first `play sequential` block and your second set under the second `play sequential` block. Make sure to include a mix of beats, bass, and leads. Use a nested loop to repeat part of your code inside one of the sections.\r\n\r\n<div style=\"background:#ebe8f1; border: 0; border-radius: 10px; clear:both; padding: 5px\">\r\n\r\nNeed some help? Try the [<i class=\"fa-solid fa-book\"></i> Docs](#clickable=documentation-button) in the upper-right corner!\r\n\r\n</div>\r\n\r\n**Reflect:** Listen to your song and iterate until it sounds the way you want it to. In order to complete this level, your remix must include:\r\n\r\n- A beat, bass, and lead track\r\n- At least 5 new unique tracks\r\n- At least 1 nested loop",
